division has been specifically created to meet current and emerging market requirements and drive continued efficiencies it has a global offering that spans the complete spectrum of commercial aviation training with services that encompass selection cadet ab initio training resourcing and airline training including recurrent type rating and command training – all supported by hightechnology simulation products such as the realityseven™ full flight simulator ctc aviation and link uk have been collaborating since the acquisition of ctc aviation by l in may 0 this dynamic team effort resulted in the successful establishment of a training facility at london’s gatwick airport uk that houses l realityseven training devices for both boeing and airbus aircraft to support a variety of customers it also yielded a highly successful partnership with virgin atlantic airways to provide a b training and instructional capability via ctc aviation instructors on a link uk b realityseven full flight simulator as a part of this consolidation the existing training portfolio of link uk has been aligned with ctc aviation’s airline training business this includes the company’s leading training facility in bangkok – the asian aviation training centre aatc – which has recently expanded from six to eight full flight simulators alan crawford president of l commercial training solutions said “l commercial training solutions offers a comprehensive valueadded portfolio to deliver uniquely targeted solutions that meet our customers’ total scope of training resourcing and simulation needs we are committed to building on the strengths that will continue to support our customers in the future our agility our drive to innovate and our firm belief in developing ongoing partnerships will enable us to consistently exceed expectations” l commercial training solutions is located in crawley uk and includes l link uk l ctc aviation and l ctc private jet it is a world leader in providing intelligent total training solutions for pilots and maintainers across a wide range of commercial platforms l commercial training solutions provides a full spectrum of stateoftheart training solutions including ab initio training airline training training centers and highfidelity simulation products the company has delivered commercial training solutions to customer locations throughout north america europe asia africa the middle east and the pacific rim headquartered in new york city l employs approximately  people worldwide and is a leading provider of a broad range of communication and electronic systems and products used on military and commercial platforms l is also a prime contractor in aerospace systems the company reported 0 sales of 0 billion to learn more about l please visit the company’s website at wwwlcomcom l uses its website as a channel of distribution of material company information financial and other material information regarding l is routinely posted on the company’s website and is readily accessible safe harbor statement under the private securities litigation reform act of except for historical information contained herein the matters set forth in this news release are forwardlooking statements statements that are predictive in nature that depend upon or refer to events or conditions or that include words such as “expects” “anticipates” “intends” “plans” “believes” “estimates” “will” “could” and similar expressions are forwardlooking statements the forwardlooking statements set forth above involve a number of risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from any such statement including the risks and uncertainties discussed in the company’s safe harbor compliance statement for forwardlooking statements included in the company’s recent filings including forms 0k and 0q with the securities and exchange commission the forwardlooking statements speak only as of the date made and the company undertakes no obligation to update these forwa